  "Title": "OpenClaw: Command-authorized non-owners could reach owner-only `/config` and `/debug` surfaces",
  "Description": "OpenClaw documented `/config` and `/debug` as owner-only commands, but the command handlers checked only whether the sender was command-authorized. A lower-trust sender who was intentionally allowed to run commands could still reach privileged configuration and debugging surfaces.",
